Subject: System fails to boot 2.3.18ac8, only showing "Preparing to boot  Linux..." (no prompt is displayed).
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/1999/9/26/58

I am only able to boot a couple of times before my boot fails
where I only get the "Preparing to boot Linux..." (I'm paraphrasing).
Anyhow, I never get the boot prompt that allows me to select 
a kernel.
If I then boot from the rescue floppy set, e2fsck /dev/hda5,
set up the ability to boot /mnt/hda5, mount it and run:
	lilo -C /etc/lilo.conf -b /dev/hda5 -r /mnt/hda5
the lilo gets reinstalled successfully.  Then, I run sync
and umount /mnt/hda5 and reboot.  The system invariably 
boots successfully afterwards.  Then, after a couple
boots, the boot fails, only showing "Preparing to boot Linux..."
I am running the latest Rawhide stuff from 
rawhide.redhat.com and kernel 2.3.18ac8.
LILO version 21, Copyright 1992-1998 Werner Almesberger
